old man
Homonym Number:
Word Class:adjective
Sense Number:
Definition:long-lasting, persistent, or in some way large or outstanding of its kind: `old man couch grass'; `an old man southerly'; `an old man snapper'; `an old man flood'. (occas. spg old-man; occ. caps.) superior, large, remarkable (of its kind) (cf GRANDFATHER) esp. withnatural objects se also OLD MAN FLOOD,
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
