Date: 11/11/1933
Source: Press, The
Author:
Vol / Page: 15
Edition:
Quote: Old man.- Slang. Striking, big, remarkable, e.g. an o.m. rock, flood,  nor'-wester, cabbage tree, etc. Hence the o.m is a common name for paddocks, though some hills are probably so called from the fancied resemblance to man's face. (C.)
Notes: Acland Glossary

